title: University friends pay tribute to 'generous and kind person' killed in Titan sub implosion
description: The university friends of the 19-year-old who was killed in the Titan sub implosion have paid tribute to the "incredibly generous and kind person".

title: Tropical storms form amid forecast of heavy rain and winds in Caribbean
description: Two tropical storms have formed in the Atlantic in June for the first time since records began.

title: Wagner boss accuses Russian military leaders of targeting his troops
description: The head of the Wagner mercenary group has accused Russian military leaders of targeting his troops.

title: The Paris climate summit was an important moment - but the wait goes on for concrete decisions
description: President Emmanuel Macron's climate finance summit in Paris has delivered some progress on a number of headline issues.

title: It was once Europe's second biggest reservoir - now it's nearly empty and threatening the world's food supply
description: For seven decades a vast reservoir has dominated the landscape here as Europe's second biggest.

title: Steps turn down gig in Dubai over country's 'archaic' LGBT+ laws
description: Steps have refused to play a gig in Dubai because the contract stipulated there should be "no mention of sexuality," band member Ian "H" Watkins has said.

title: Ireland TV boss suspended amid scandal over payments to star
description: The boss of Irish broadcaster RTE has been suspended amid a controversy over misreporting the salary of its highest paid star.

title: Billionaire reveals texts showing he was offered 'last minute price' tickets for Titanic sub's doomed journey
description: A billionaire was offered cut-price tickets for him and his son to go on the Titan submersible on its fateful final journey - but turned them down due to scheduling issues.

title: Texts reveal last-minute price ticket offer to billionaire for sub's doomed journey
description: A billionaire was offered cut-price tickets to embark on Titan's ill-fated voyage - but backed out because of scheduling issues.

title: Who is the 7ft 4in teenager being touted as the NBA's next biggest star?
description: Victor Wembanyama - who is listed at 7ft 4in tall and has an 8ft wingspan - is being touted as a future NBA star.

title: Expert explains why the Titan submersible may have suffered 'catastrophic implosion'
description: A former Royal Navy submarine captain has explained the possible reasons for the "catastrophic implosion" suffered by the Titan submersible on its descent to the wreck of the Titanic.

title: UFC boss says Zuckerberg and Musk 'dead serious' about cage fight
description: Mark Zuckerberg and Elon Musk are "absolutely dead serious" about fighting each other in a cage match, the boss of UFC has said.

title: Russian diplomat squatting on axed embassy site
description: Australia's prime minister has described a Russian diplomat squatting on land near the country's parliament as "a bloke standing in the cold on a bit of grass in Canberra" who poses "no threat" to security.

title: Titanic director said he 'knew submersible was destroyed' four days before debris found
description: Titanic director James Cameron has claimed he knew the Titan submersible had been destroyed less than 24 hours after the vessel lost contact.

title: Obesity patients made to feel like 'second-class citizens' as demand for Ozempic soars
description: People battling chronic obesity are facing stigmatisation as they try to obtain the much-vaunted drug Ozempic amid shortages in Ireland and elsewhere, according to doctors.

title: Student, 19, killed in Titan was 'terrified' before trip but went as a Father's Day present
description: The 19-year-old university student who was killed in the Titan submersible was "terrified" before the trip but went as a Father's Day present.
